  - var name = 'Louisiana'
  - var path = 'louisiana'

block content

  +state(name, path, 'The Pelican State', 'April 30, 1812')

  .intro
    p Louisiana has flown many flags in its history, like the flags of Spain, France, and Great Britain. Leading up to and during the American Civil War, it flew four distinct flags including the Confederate battle and national flags.
    p Its distinct pelican flag was flown during the war, but it was not officially adopted until 1912. Variations were inevitable, many not including the three droplets of blood on the pelican’s chest. In 2006, the flag (and state seal) design was formalized and standardized.
    p This official version was adopted November 22, 2010.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Louisiana flag features a field of blue charged with a crest, centered.
      p The crest depicts a mother pelican with her three chicks in a nest, wounding herself with three drops of blood on her chest.
      p Upon a white banner below the crest, the state motto, “Union Justice Confidence” is inscribed.
      +survey(name, '36th')
    .visual.flag
      +flag(name, path)

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      p The brown pelican is indigenous to Lousiana, but the symbology is also tied to Europe and Christian tradition. Described as “in her piety,” the pelican became a symbol of the Eucharist, where followers consume the blood of Christ in celebration of his sacrifice.
      p Pelicans were often observed as stabbing themselves with their bills, giving them a reputation of being attentive, self-sacrificing mothers.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-louisiana-icon-pelican.svg', alt='a mother pelican with blood drops on her chest looks over her nest and three babies')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The pelican has long been a symbol of Lousiana. Prior to the Civil War, the “pelican in her piety” was paired with the words “Justice Union and Confidence.”
      p After the war, when union and reconstruction were priority, the order was changed to “Union Justice Confidence.”
    .visual.flag
      +coat-of-arms(name, path)

